## REACT ENVIRONMENT CONSTRAINTS

React is loaded from CDN at runtime — it is a GLOBAL, not an import.
```javascript
// TOP OF FILE (line 1) — keep exactly:
import { useState, useEffect, useCallback, useRef, useMemo } from "react";
// This import is STRIPPED by the build script and replaced with:
const { useState, useEffect, useCallback, useRef, useMemo } = React;
```

- NEVER add `import React from 'react'` — it will break the build
- NEVER use JSX automatic runtime (`jsx: 'react-jsx'`)
- NEVER use `ReactDOM.render()` — use `ReactDOM.createRoot().render()`
- Always use `React.createElement(ComponentName)` at mount point (not JSX)

