## AUTHENTICATION ARCHITECTURE

Two-layer auth system:

### Layer 1 — Local (localStorage/sessionStorage) — Lines 1–510
```
AUTH_ACCOUNTS_KEY = "dispatch-hq-accounts"  → localStorage → array of UserAccount
AUTH_SESSION_KEY  = "dispatch-hq-session"   → sessionStorage → single SessionObject
```
Used for offline/demo mode. Admin account created on first run by `ensureAdminExists()` (L60).

### Layer 2 — Server (GAS) — Lines 1714+
```
DispatcherApp state: authStatus, currentUser (with .token from GAS)
saveSession(userData), clearSession()
```
GAS sessions: 24h TTL, 64-char hex token stored in Sessions sheet.

Password hashing:
- Client (Layer 2): `SHA-256(password + "dispatch-hq-client-salt")` via Web Crypto
- GAS server: re-hashes with PBKDF2 10,000 rounds before storage
- Local (Layer 1): `SHA-256(salt + password + "dispatch-hq-2024")` via Web Crypto

Admin credentials:
- username: `admin` (hardcoded, unreservable)
- password hash: set `ADMIN_PASSWORD_HASH` in GAS after running `hashPassword("pass")` in console

