## GAS API — COMPLETE CONTRACT

**Transport:** All POST use `Content-Type: text/plain;charset=utf-8`, body = `JSON.stringify(payload)`
**CORS:** text/plain = simple request = no preflight = GAS receives POST directly

```
GET  ?action=ping&token=AUTH_TOKEN
     → { success, message, sheetName, recordCount }

GET  ?action=list&token=AUTH_TOKEN[&since=ISO]
     → { success, records: [{id, encryptedData, iv, salt, timestamp, deleted}], count }

GET  ?action=validateSession&sessionToken=TOKEN
     → { success, valid: bool }

GET  ?action=adminGetUsers&sessionToken=TOKEN   (admin role required)
     → { success, users: User[], activeSessions, totalBookings }

POST { action:"register", username, passwordHash, displayName, email }
     → { success, status:"pending", message }

POST { action:"login", username, passwordHash }
     → { success, token, expiresAt, role, displayName }
     error 401: wrong credentials
     error 403: pending/disabled account

POST { action:"logout", sessionToken }
     → { success }

POST { action:"approveUser"|"rejectUser"|"disableUser"|"enableUser"|"deleteUser",
       targetUsername, sessionToken }    (admin session required)
     → { success, message }

POST { action:"batchSync", records: EncRecord[], clientId, token }
     max 500 records, AUTH_TOKEN required
     → { success, created, updated, totalRecords }

POST { action:"delete", id, clientId, token }
     → { success, deleted: id }          soft-delete only

POST { action:"purge", confirmPurge:true, token }
     1-hour cooldown enforced via CacheService
     → { success, purged: count }        hard-deletes soft-deleted rows
```

---

## GAS SHEETS SCHEMA

```
Sheet: EncryptedBookings
  id | encryptedData (≤50KB) | iv (base64) | salt (base64) | timestamp (ISO) | deleted ("true"/"false")

Sheet: Users
  id | username | passwordHash | displayName | role | status | createdAt | approvedAt | approvedBy | email

Sheet: Sessions
  token | userId | username | role | createdAt | expiresAt | ip

Sheet: SyncMeta
  key | value | updatedAt

Sheet: SyncLog
  timestamp | action | clientId | recordCount | details
```

