## SECURITY — INVARIANTS CURSOR MUST NEVER BREAK

```javascript
// 1. Always sanitize on submit:
sanitize(form.customerName)
sanitizePhone(form.phone)
sanitizeNumeric(form.paymentAmount)
sanitizeDriverId(form.driverNumber)

// 2. Sync URL domain check — must stay:
if (!url.startsWith("https://script.google.com/")) { reject }

// 3. isValidBooking uses hasOwnProperty (not `in` operator):
Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(b, "__proto__") // block prototype pollution

// 4. BANNED: eval(), dangerouslySetInnerHTML, alert(), confirm(), document.write

// 5. Error messages must be sanitized before display:
sanitizeErrorMsg(err) // strips URLs, file paths, tokens ≥32 chars

// 6. GAS rate limit key MUST be "rate_global" (not client-supplied value)

// 7. All GAS LockService.waitLock() inside try/catch, releaseLock() in finally

// 8. Passphrase: min 8, max 128 chars. Never store plaintext.

// 9. No raw_info or stack traces in user-facing error messages
```

